[b]TVO - Allan Gregg in Conversation: Margaret Somerville addresses contentious ethical issues[/b]

Margaret Somerville is one of Canada's leading ethicists. She is founding director of the Centre for Medicine, Ethics and Law at McGill University. In her book &quot;The Ethical Imagination: Journeys of the Human Spirit&quot;, she tackles issues such as same-sex marriage and stem cell research. (Original broadcast December 2003)

